Cray Research Inc said it installeda Cray X-MP/14 supercomputer valued at eight mln dlrs atGrumman Corp's Grumman Aerospace Corp.    Cray said the system, which includes a 550 solid statestorage device, was installed in the first quarter at Grumman'sscientific computer facility in Bethpage, N.Y.    The system replaces a Cray-1M/2300 computer systeminstalled in 1983. It will be used for engineering andscientific applications in the design of aircraft systems. Reuter&#3;